      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Berkeley_Township%2C_New_Jersey"
    },
    {
      "id": 2,
      "text": "Before Europeans, the Lenni‑Lenape Unalachtigo tribe called the area the “People who live near the ocean.”",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        5
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 2"
      ],
      "source": "https://grokipedia.com/page/holiday_city_berkeley_new_jersey"
    },
    {
      "id": 3,
      "text": "The town sits about 43 feet above sea level, making it prone to coastal flooding.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        3
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 2"
      ],
      "source": "https://grokipedia.com/page/holiday_city_berkeley_new_jersey"
    },
    {
      "id": 4,
      "text": "Cedar sawmills once dominated, turning swamps into productive farmland before deforestation reshaped the landscape.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        9
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 2"
      ],
      "source": "https://grokipedia.com/page/holiday_city_berkeley_new_jersey"
    },
    {
      "id": 5,
      "text": "The Royal Pines Hotel, built for $1.175 million, once hosted wealthy vacationers and later served as a nursing home.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        20
